 Diskussionen zum Thema zur Verfügung. "Insgesamt eine höchst informative, thematisch breit angelegte, faktenreiche Arbeit, die als Einstieg, keinesfalls aber als Schlusspunkt des Diskurses zur strafrechtlichen Aufarbeitung überwundener Unrechtssysteme von großem Wert sein dürfte." (Juristische Rundschau Nr. 8/2000, S. 349f.)  aThe new edition of this standard work provides a complete account of criminal law responses to GDR-era injustices 30 years after the fall of the Berlin wall. It expands and deepens the conclusions of the first edition and incorporates all of the legal decisions and critical positions adopted since. It also considers the role of transitional justice in overcoming systemic injustices.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzGermany (East)xHistory. 0aCriminal lawzGermany (East)xHistory. 0aPolitical crimes and offenseszGermany (East) 0aPolitical crimes and offenseszGermany (East). 0aPolitical rehabilitationxLaw and legislationzGermany (East). 0aPolitical rehabilitationzGermany (East). 0aReparation (Criminal justice)zGermany (East) 0aReparation (Criminal justice)zGermany (East). 0aRule of lawzGermany (East)xHistory. 0aTransitional justicezGermanyxHistory. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC0 cEPUBz97831105937780 cprintz978311057394740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311059735640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110597356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110597356/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  